      </svg></div>
      <div class="stack-lg">
        <p class="t-lead t-pretty">Nothing in you is happening alone. The food you ate, the sleep you didn't get, the conversation that ended without resolution, the season the soil is in — all of it is in the room with you, whether you noticed it or not.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty">This is not a moral claim. It is a physical one. You are porous. So is everything else. Influence moves in both directions, all the time, and most of it never asks permission first.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty">The work is not to know every connection. The work is to remember, often enough, that there <em>are</em> connections — and to act, in small ways, as if there are.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

